fields.problem_background: Despite the fact that TB is a leading cause of death among people living with HIV, active TB case finding is often not included in HIV programs. As a result, many TB cases are being missed, leading to prolonged illness and increased mortality. This CQI project aims to develop and implement strategies to improve active TB case finding in HIV programs, with the aim of increasing the number of TB cases identified and treated in a timely manner.
fields.objective: increasing the number of TB cases identified and treated in a timely manner; enhancing collaboration between HIV and TB programs; improving access and quality of care for TB patients.

fields.description: The "Quality Improvement Training - Participants Workbook" is a guide for individuals taking part in a training program aimed at improving quality within an organization. It covers various aspects of quality management, such as setting goals and standards, monitoring performance, and implementing continuous improvement processes. The workbook includes exercises and activities to reinforce key concepts, as well as tools and templates to help participants apply what they've learned to their own work. The goal of the training program is to equip participants with the knowledge and skills they need to drive quality improvement within their organization.

fields.resource_name: KENYA QUALITY IMPROVEMENT FRAMEWORK - TRAINING COURSE GUIDE
fields.description: The "Kenya Quality Improvement Framework - Training Course Guide" is a comprehensive training program designed to help organizations in Kenya improve the quality of their services and products. The course covers the key principles of quality management and provides practical tools and techniques for achieving quality improvement. The guide covers topics such as setting quality goals and standards, monitoring performance, and implementing continuous improvement processes. The course also provides opportunities for participants to apply what they've learned through exercises, case studies, and group activities. The ultimate aim of the Kenya Quality Improvement Framework training is to equip organizations with the knowledge and skills they need to drive quality improvement and deliver high-quality services and products to their customers.

fields.problem_or_opportunity: To develop and implement strategies to improve active TB case finding in HIV programs, to increase the number of TB cases identified and treated in a timely manner.
fields.key_successes: Increased awareness of TB among HIV program staff and clients; Improved collaboration between HIV and TB staff; Increased testing and early diagnosis of TB cases among HIV-positive individuals.
fields.challenges: Limited resources and financial support; lack of knowledge and skills among staff; difficulty in accessing and engaging hard-to-reach individuals.
fields.best_practices: Establishing multi-sectoral partnerships between HIV and TB programs; using mobile health technology to increase testing and early diagnosis; providing training and capacity building for staff.
fields.recommendations: Develop a comprehensive TB screening and treatment protocol for HIV programs; ensure adequate resources and financial support; use creative strategies to engage hard-to-reach individuals.
fields.resources: Financial resources; human resources; technical expertise; mobile health technology; data management systems.
fields.future_plans: Monitor and evaluate the impact of the CQI project; review and update protocols and procedures; continue to build partnerships between HIV and TB programs; explore new strategies for engaging hard-to-reach individuals.
